{
    "title": "Postgres DBM - Query metrics collection (legacy vs optimized)",
    "description": "Tells the end-to-end story of the **statement metrics** collection algorithm, stage by stage, so you can see where time and work go each cycle and compare `query_metrics.incremental_query_metrics: false` (legacy full `pg_stat_statements` load) vs `true` (optimized collector).\n\n### How to read this dashboard\nGroups are ordered to match the actual pipeline in `statements_v2.py._collect_metrics_rows`:\n\n1. **pgss capacity / usage / eviction** — the source table's health (`max`, `count`, `dealloc`). Drives everything downstream.\n2. **Per-cycle latency overview** — headline timings to compare v1 vs v2.\n3. **Stage 1 · Snapshot load** — column probe + the main pgss read.\n4. **Stage 2 · Change detection (delta)** — how many rows/queryids actually changed.\n5. **Stage 3 · Obfuscation resolve** — cache hit/miss and the miss-path cost (text fetch + FFI obfuscation).\n6. **Stage 4 · Assembly & output** — merged output rows + full job time.\n7. **Health & errors** — per-operation and pgss-config errors.\n\n### Template variables\n- **database_instance** — filters by the `database_instance` tag (DBM instance identifier).\n- **cluster_name** — filters by the `cluster_name` tag (Agent/host orchestrator context, **not** PostgreSQL's `cluster_name` setting). Use `*` for all.\n\n### Metric namespaces\n- `@tracked_method` timings: histogram **`postgresql.dd.postgres.operation.time.avg`** (ms) tagged **`operation:<method>`**; result sizes via **`postgresql.dd.postgres.operation.result.length`**; errors via **`postgresql.dd.postgres.operation.error`**.\n- v2 throughput gauges are emitted raw (no `postgresql.` prefix): **`dd.postgres.statement_metrics.lookup.*`**, **`dd.postgres.statement_metrics.delta.*`**, **`dd.postgres.queries.query_rows_raw`**, **`dd.postgres.statement_metrics.error`**.\n- pgss housekeeping (prefixed): **`postgresql.pg_stat_statements.max`** (gauge), **`postgresql.pg_stat_statements.count`** (count), **`postgresql.pg_stat_statements.dealloc`** (count, PG14+).\n\n---\n*Generated for integrations-core Postgres DBM development.*",
    "layout_type": "ordered",
    "template_variables": [
        {
            "name": "database_instance",
            "prefix": "database_instance",
            "default": "*"
        },
        {
            "name": "cluster_name",
            "prefix": "cluster_name",
            "default": "*"
        }
    ],
    "widgets": [
        {
            "definition": {
                "title": "Stage 0 · pgss capacity, usage & eviction",
                "type": "group",
                "layout_type": "ordered",
                "background_color": "vivid_blue",
                "widgets": [
                    {
                        "definition": {
                            "type": "note",
                            "content": "The source `pg_stat_statements` table is fixed-size (`pg_stat_statements.max`). When full, Postgres **deallocates** least-used entries (`dealloc`). High fill % + rising dealloc means query-text churn, which drives obfuscation cache misses downstream (Stage 3).",
                            "background_color": "blue",
                            "font_size": "14",
                            "text_align": "left",
                            "vertical_align": "top",
                            "show_tick": false,
                            "tick_pos": "50%",
                            "tick_edge": "left",
                            "has_padding": true
                        }
                    },
                    {
                        "definition": {
                            "title": "pgss fill — entries (count) vs capacity (max)",
                            "type": "timeseries",
                            "requests": [
                                {
                                    "response_format": "timeseries",
                                    "queries": [
                                        {
                                            "data_source": "metrics",
                                            "name": "cnt",
                                            "query": "avg:postgresql.pg_stat_statements.count{$database_instance,$cluster_name} by {database_instance}",
                                            "semantic_mode": "combined"
                                        }
                                    ],
                                    "formulas": [
                                        {
                                            "formula": "cnt",
                                            "alias": "Entries (count)"
                                        }
                                    ]
                                },
                                {
                                    "response_format": "timeseries",
                                    "queries": [
                                        {
                                            "data_source": "metrics",
                                            "name": "mx",
                                            "query": "avg:postgresql.pg_stat_statements.max{$database_instance,$cluster_name} by {database_instance}",
                                            "semantic_mode": "combined"
                                        }
                                    ],
                                    "formulas": [
                                        {
                                            "formula": "mx",
                                            "alias": "Capacity (max)"
                                        }
                                    ],
                                    "style": {
                                        "line_type": "dashed"
                                    }
                                }
                            ]
                        }
                    },
                    {
                        "definition": {
                            "title": "pgss fill ratio (%) — count / max",
                            "type": "timeseries",
                            "requests": [
                                {
                                    "response_format": "timeseries",
                                    "queries": [
                                        {
                                            "data_source": "metrics",
                                            "name": "cnt",
                                            "query": "avg:postgresql.pg_stat_statements.count{$database_instance,$cluster_name} by {database_instance}",
                                            "semantic_mode": "combined"
                                        },
                                        {
                                            "data_source": "metrics",
                                            "name": "mx",
                                            "query": "avg:postgresql.pg_stat_statements.max{$database_instance,$cluster_name} by {database_instance}",
                                            "semantic_mode": "combined"
                                        }
                                    ],
                                    "formulas": [
                                        {
                                            "formula": "100 * cnt / mx",
                                            "alias": "Fill %"
                                        }
                                    ]
                                }
                            ],
